6:
Why... Why does this terrible monster
know my name?!
19:
*sigh* The mental damage I took
from that was way more than the
physical...
27:
I thought so... It's that weird plushie
again.
31:
It looks like SOMEONE forced sprites
into it in order to make it move.
35:
Yeah... But this doll wasn't made as a
weapon, so it shouldn't have
attacked us...
39:
Then something must have caused
it to go berserk like that.
43:
Taking advantage of the sprites in
such a way is still unforgivable!
Oooh, just thinking about it makes
my blood boil! The criminal must
pay!
48:
No kidding. Placing sprites into a
doll? Who even thinks of something
like that? Talk about creepy....
52:
...Oooh! I can't even get mad at her
right now! It's not fair!
62:
Oho... So this is the drifting island the
rumors speak of!
66:
Aaalk!
Shyweee!
Can you hear me?!
75:
The firepit is still warm... It appears
we are on the right track!
80:
These footprints go farther into the
island. Quickly, we must—
84:
This is Light on Paradise Isle. Nimbus,
do you read me?
88:
Yeah. We just landed on that drifting
island you were telling us about.
90:
We found footprints and a fire that
we think Alk and Shywe left behind.
We're about to start searching now.
93:
Excellent! I'm glad you found them.
Eclair and the others should be right
behind you.
96: Got it. Then we'll continue on ahead.
101:
According to the information Selene
procured for us, that island is far
more dangerous than we initially
thought.
103:
There's a government lab on that
island, and it houses the most
terrible of specimens, found in the
northern seas...
105:
A living sample of the Devourer of
Stars!
112:
Ah, that's it! That is the building 
I woke up in!
116:
A hospital? No, wait, it looks more
like a research lab... What's THIS
doing on such a tiny little island?
120:
It doesn't appear to be abandoned...
We should be able to find someone
here.
124:
Yeah, but... don't let your guard
down just yet.
132:
No, but... the connection felt a little
stronger than before.
136:
See? I told you that you'd get better
in no time.
153:
Me neither, but all the lights and
stuff are still on. This place definitely
isn't deserted...
158: Ah, this is where I woke up!
167:
The HELL was with that nutjob?!
What a WASTE OF TIME!
170:
A ritual to wake up some overgrown
octopod? PLEASE. My research into
growing a luscious fur coat is a
BAJILLION times more important!
174:
AAARRRGH! I can't BELIEVE I came all
the way here for NOTHING! I should—
181: ...Hehe, I guess it's not TOO bad.
184:
I'd rather practice going on a
seaside vacation with my
Nimby-Wimby than hang out with
some dumb eggheads anyway!
192:
I don't know... who you think you're
dealing with, but... get out...
199:
Dammit... Pissing me off... I need...
fur...
213:
H-hello, sir! We're sorry we entered
without permission, but—
221:
I don't think this man will be much
help... He's clearly not well...
229:
...Let's head further inside. Maybe
we'll find a clue as to what's going
on.
237:
It seems the followers of the
Devourer of Stars and a faction of
the Gaean government are
conducting secret experiments on
that island...
241:
Those madmen are attempting to
use transmutation to transcend the
limits of humanity!
